  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - SHAMAN</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>KICK ALL ASS(LVLS 34 AND UP)</font> - <small>Mecbeth Fyresoul, Rallos Zek</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'>Ok,playing on a pvp server I have learned many techniques on how to kill people, especially since my best character is a lvl 34 shaman. We as Shamans are gods in PvP. We equal necroc dots and have adequete DDs. At lvl 34 I do 251dmg, a wizard I think does 300 or so, no big deal when 1 heal does that as well. And I can stack for 600dmg in Dots. Well anyways.....to the fighting.<P>
 When fighting a melee class it is important to always MALISE THEM!!! All melee classes have some sort of concentration in to resistances, blood stained mantle and such sort, malisement(lvl 34 malise spell) cuts all resistances by 37 except disease, because it is disease based. When a SK or whatever has 12 sv cold, 21 sv magic, -17 sv poison, life will be much easier for u. Throw on ur 2 dots, and watch half their life die, keep em rooted, quicken ur pet and send him into melee. If the meleer gets close he will be hitting u for about 50,50. SO make sure to also keep him blinded(i mean its only 12mana). If he cant see anything, and then all of a sudden hes unblinded and half of his life is gone he's scared shitless. Your pet will do good dmg if it is a blue one, so make sure. U wont need to dot again because since his cold resist will be extra low, ur DD will do good damage(even with the DD cut, DAMN U VERANT!!!) that's all u will need for melee classes unless it is a paladin, so conserve mana for them.
<P>
     Now for casters, they are a different story. We dont like anyone who can blast for equal to greater than us. Wizards are maybe the easiest to deal with. Make sure u have a pet, quicken him, as soon as the duel begins, BLIND, then malisement(cause all casters have resistance buffs), send ur pet in to melee, the secret is to get up close and not let up, keep him rooted, cause when ur pet is doing 30,30,10 every 2 seconds and we can throw in a 20-30 or so every 3 secs he wont be able to get a spell off. IF he comes close slam him and it will stun and interupt him. Throw on the 2 dots, casters have weak Hps, about 700 or so at lvl 35, so the dots will weaken him REAL low, then 2 blasts should finish him. The other 3 casting classes r different. A whole new stratagey, cause they got pets too. U will want to blind them and root their pet, bring u and ur pet to the caster, repeat as above. Malise, blind, dots, blind, DD,blind, DD, blind, etc, etc, etc. If their pet comes loose try ur best to detain it. IF fightin an enchanters make sure u got as high MR as possible, cause THEY WILL tashani u, keep em blind so they cant, and so they cant mez u. Necros r the hardest to fight out of anyone in my opinion. 1 reason, lifetap, u can dot them all u want, then can lifetap u, make sure they ARE ALWAYS BLINDED!!!! ALWAYS!!! dot em and keep the DDs up, detain the pet and u should be good.
<P>
     These plans have worked for me, and hopefully they will work for u, the best thing about a shaman is that we peak at lvl 50. Many classes have ups and downs through their lvls, we start low and do nothing but get better, and lvl 50 not much anyone can do to ya. GOOD LUCK!!!!!

		</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'>&nbsp;</td></tr>
